  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><strong>Charisma Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure: </strong>Target has disadvantage on &amp;reference[constitution] and &amp;reference[death saving throws]. Target cannot benefit from abilities that prevent them from reaching 0 hit points, and if they reach 0 hit points, they are &amp;reference[incapacitated] for 1 minute even if they later regain hit points.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success: </strong>No effect.</p></li></ul></div><p></p><p><em>This functions to block a zombie's @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-creatures.Actor.iyBmfvksjNJz5ueD.Item.RDeCoZRniQBNq0rX]{Undead Fortitude}, an orc's @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-ancestries.Item.iM3hmD5dtPEsv6UA]{Relentless Endurance}, and other similar effects. It blocks @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.3Dpyp708Lxvq4niO]{Death Ward}'s ability to prevent you from hitting 0, but does not prevent Death Ward from blocking instant death. A regenerating creature, such as a troll, can still regenerate after reaching 0 with this curse, but would be temporarily incapacitated.</em></p>",
      "chat": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p><strong>Charisma Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure: </strong>Target has disadvantage on &amp;reference[constitution] saving throws. If target reaches 0 hit points, they die, even if they would normally survive.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success: </strong>No effect.</p></li></ul></div>"
    },
